gravel.name: Gate Loops Direct Burial EL 36-100
gravel.description: The EL 36-100 Direct Burial Exit Loop is used in installations under concrete, asphalt or gravel roads and the wire used is UL 493 certified and designed for burial application. BD Loops - Exit Loop - 6' X 12' Direct Burial Performed Loops with 100' Lead  Used for installations under concrete, asphalt, pavers, or gravel roads. The most common installation is the loop tied directly to the rebar before concrete is poured. Wire is UL 493 certified designed for a direct burial application.Unlike loops wrapped through PVC, The BD Loops Direct Burial Loop does not have an air pocket resulting in fewer repeat service calls due to phantom detections caused by ground vibration. Built with a high quality solid 14AWG wire out performing other preformed loops with twice as much copper per foot and increased tensile strength.Solid 14AWG wire also results in the direct burial loop being very ridged giving the installer the opportunity to easily set-up and layout the loop and prevents the loop from falling in-between the rebar patter. Twisted jacketed lead-in prevents “coil back” from normal twisted lead-in, preventing wasted time untangling lead-in wires. The loop wire has arrows indicating the direction of current allowing easy understanding of phasing.Each direct burial loop comes with an installation kit including easy to understand instructions, cable ties for installation on top of redbar, ground stakes for under gravel roads, and stickers for easy identification after the loops have been installed.            Feature	BenefitsThicker 14-gauge loop wire, 4 times more copper than 20-gauge wire.	More copper means a better performing loop and increased tensile strength.UL 493 Direct burial rated loop wire.	Insurance the right product is being used for the job resulting in an immense lifespanLoops sold as a kit.	Supplied instructions, ground stakes, cable ties, and loop labels.Pre-phased at the factory.	Saves time and prevents confusion when installing two loops to one detector.Soldered connections	Ensure top performance over time.Flex yoke design pre-fitted with ½ inch PVC coupler.	Saves installation time and material cost.No air pocket in loop wire design.	Will not float to surface during a concrete pour and also eliminates faults trips due to ground vibrations.Compact size and reduced weight.	Saves on shipping cost and warehouse space.

fix up.description: 2003 Acura CL S-Type130K Original MilesSecond OwnerVtec V6 280horsepower / 5spd AutoHigh performance upgradesUpgraded TransmissionFully servicedCustom stereoClean CarfaxFresh smog and tags are good to September. Title is in hand, and in my namePlease read whole ad before calling, as many questions can be answered belowClean Carfax Shows:No accidents, 2 owner, Clean Title, accurate mileage20 service records from Acura of Stockton from original owner. The original transmissions went out at 100k. However a 2006/2007 Honda Accord V6 uses the same exact trans, except Honda fixed the fatal flaw (2/3rd gear clutch pack oiling) and they are very dependable. I installed a trans out of a 2007 accord that was 1 owner from Dublin, always maintained at Honda with also 100K on the odometer (came out of a salvaged crash car was hit in rear) This trans should last the life of the car without issue. This is a common swap among CL and TL enthusiasts.Along with trans, around 100K I installed a Genuine  Acura Timing belt and water pump kit with tensioner and seals.  All Factory parts. I also did factory Iridium spark plugs and checked the valve adjustment at that time.All 4 brakes are done recently with e-coated rotors, stoptech pads and flushed performance brake fluid2 new motor mounts, Factory AcuraCoolant replaced and power steering fluid flushed with Honda fluidNew HID Ballasts and bulbsNow for the goodies $$*Koni Yellow Rebound adjustable Struts at all 4 corners with stock springs at 1 lower height *Eibach Sway Bars front and rear with poly bushings* All 4 sway bar end links replaced with HD Moog greasable units*Poly strut rod mounts*Real Deal Comptech Stainless Mufflers and Y pipe (can be showroom polished if wanted)*Air sound/restrictor removed from air box (still smog legal no issue, just throatier sound)*Has TL rims on it as opposed to the factory CL rims which look almost identical except the CL rims get curbed easier and don't have the nice dark metallic background color. *Interior has been double dyna-matted (sound deadening) all along back seat area, both doors completely, trunk *Has custom stereo with a 10 Sub with a JL amp powering it, and a 4 channel rockford fosgate powering door speakers and 6x9s, all quality cables throughout even all the way up to the door speakers*Ceramic 20% tinted windows all the way around, nice privacy but  not so dark can't see out and they are the heat resistant pricey ceramicThis CL Runs and Drives excellent, super clean and tasteful. Handles on rails, super comfortable, and plenty of power along with good gas mileage. Everything works, AC cold, both heated seats work, windows, locks, power seats, everything. The negatives:The air bag recall needs to be done, and the seatbelt receiver replaced (both will be done for free at the dealer, I just never got around to it because its a few cities away)Dings on body (see passenger door) and minor visual defects on exterior (rock chips front bumper) 20 year old black car, its super clean and representable but its also not a complete garage queen.Will need tires soon. The current ones will get you where you need to go but theyre at the end of their life.*Price is absolutely firm, no rush to sell, if you like what you see and read you won't be wasting your time coming to see and but this clean machine.*Cody

loud.name: Carr Rambler (2002)
loud.description: New tubes recently from manufacturer. The Carr Rambler Amp is one of the earliest designs from Carr Amplifiers, and is still one of their most popular offerings. The Rambler gives that unmistakable American Deluxe sound, but with vastly improved clean headroom, tighter bass response, and the ability to switch between 28 watts pentode and 14 watts triode.Triode/Pentode Switch - Changes the way the output tubes operate. Pentode sounds loud and punchy with great headroom while Triode is more vintage and warm with very thick midrange. The Pentode mode is the Rambler's full power setting, producing 28 watts. The Triode mode makes 14 watts.The Rambler is Carr Amplifiers' shot at offering a classic 1x12 combo for small gig/club settings with appropriate headroom, reverb, and tremolo. The Rambler has been described as having a full, rounded tone with a great threshold for clean sounds; also making it a fantastic pedal platform for those of us addicted to overdrive and fuzz pedals. Many Carr owners regard the Rambler as one of the pinnacle club amps with a great palette of tone for any player and any style.Specifications:Power Output:  28 Watts in Pentode Mode, and 14 Watts in TriodeOutput Tubes:  2 x 6L6, Cathode Biased Class A OperationPreamp Tubes:  3 x 12AX7, 1 x 12AT7    Controls    Volume, Treble, Mid, Bass, Reverb, Tremolo Depth, Tremolo SpeedSwitches:      Pentode / TriodeDims & Weight:    21 Wide x 17 High x 9 Depth at Top (10 at bottom) - 40 lbsSpeaker Config: Kingpin 50 12 - 8 OhmsFootswitch for turning Tremolo On/Off Included

famous.name: MXR CSP102SL Script Dyna Comp Reissue
famous.description: Selling a mint-condition MXR CSP102SL Script Dyna Comp Reissue pedal in original box. This was a very recent purchase but I no longer have the need for a compression pedal.
